br.com.stone.posandroid.hal.api.mifare

Class Mifare

  • br.com.stone.posandroid.hal.api.mifare.Mifare

  • public class Mifare

    Class for handling Mifare cards, from search to activation and data operations. Note that data operations take "sector" as parameter. This means that block numbers go from 0 to 3, while sector numbers may vary between card types. In some platforms, block numbers are continuous, this means that the following formula should be applied: absBlock = (sector * 4) + block

      • detectCards

        public void detectCards(@NotNull
                        MifareCardCallback mifareCallback)

        Wait for card to be presented, firing success callbacks if a Mifare card is presented, or error otherwise. It is desirable that non-Mifare cards are ignored. Turn-on Contactless module if needed.
